-- Copper Advances in London on Speculation Over Rising Demand: LME Preview
-- Claudia Carpenter
-- 2010-07-09T06:59:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/copper-advances-in-london-on-speculation-over-rising-demand-lme-preview.html

          
          
             Copper climbed in London for the
fifth time in six days on speculation that a decline in
stockpiles to a seven-month low indicated rising demand for the
metal used in pipes, tubes and wires.  
 Market News:  
 Metals News:  
 Metal Prices:  

 
-- Copper rose 1.5 percent to $6,714 a metric ton on the London
Metal Exchange at 7:30 a.m. Relative Strength Index 53.6.
-- Aluminum added 0.6 percent to $2,000 a ton. RSI 52.
-- Zinc advanced 0.4 percent to $1,862 a ton. RSI 52.6.
-- Lead increased 0.4 percent at $1,835 a ton. RSI 55.
-- Nickel climbed 0.3 percent to $19,455 a ton. RSI 47.4.
-- Tin was unchanged at $17,550 a ton. RSI 50.4.

Other markets:      Last           % Change   % YTD
U.S. Dollar Index   83.75           -0.1       7.6
Crude oil           $75.93           0.7      -4.3
Gold                $1,198.35        0.0       9.2
MSCI World Index    1,085.88         0.1      -7.1

